# Extracted Templates

## Admin "View Details" Full Screen Modal Pattern
Used for viewing comprehensive, non-editable data from a TanStack Table row.

### Architecture
- **Trigger**: A "View Details" menu item in the Actions column of a table updates a `viewedItem` state.
- **Modal Component**: Conditionally receives the `viewedItem` and controls its open state.
- **Styling**: `DialogContent` overrides: `max-w-[100vw] h-[100dvh] w-full p-0 m-0 rounded-none bg-background/95 backdrop-blur-xl border-x-0 border-y-0 overflow-y-auto`.

### Example (BookingViewModal.tsx snippet)
```tsx
<Dialog open={isOpen} onOpenChange={(open) => !open && onClose()}>
  <DialogContent className="max-w-[100vw] h-[100dvh] w-full p-0 m-0 rounded-none sm:rounded-none bg-background/95 backdrop-blur-xl border-x-0 border-y-0 overflow-y-auto">
    <div className="mx-auto w-full max-w-5xl p-6 lg:p-12">
       {/* Headers and Grid Layouts go here */}
    </div>
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```
